				"description": "\nThe API endpoint allows you to create a new task by sending an HTTP POST request to 127.0.0.1:5005/api/tasks/. The request should include a JSON payload in the raw request body with the following parameters:\n- \"title\": (string) The title of the task.\n- \"description\": (string) The description of the task.\n- \"status\": (string) The status of the task, which can be one of \"pending\", \"completed\", or \"in_progress\".\n\n### Response\nThe response to this request is in the form of a JSON schema. The HTTP status code is 201, and the Content-Type is application/json. The response body includes the following fields:\n- \"result\": An object containing the details of the newly created task, including \"id\", \"title\", \"description\", \"status\", \"created_at\", and \"updated_at\".\n- \"success\": A boolean value indicating the success of the request.\n- \"code\": An integer representing the status code of the response.\n- \"validation_errors\": A null value, indicating no validation errors.\n- \"error\": A null value, indicating no error.\n\nExample response:\n```json\n{\n  \"result\": {\n    \"id\": \"\",\n    \"title\": \"\",\n    \"description\": \"\",\n    \"status\": \"\",\n    \"created_at\": \"\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"\"\n  },\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"code\": 0,\n  \"validation_errors\": null,\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```\n"
